Bring a large #pot{} of water to a rapid boil. Rinse your @Brown Basmati Rice{2} well under cold running water. Add the rice to the boiling water and cook for ~{25%minutes} or until cooked.

> Tip: Make sure the water is rapidly boiling or else it'll take longer to cook.

Peel the @onion{1} and cut in half through the root, then roughly chop. Peel and finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}. Roughly chop the @red pepper{1}(roughly chopped). Roughly chop the @green pepper{1}(roughly chopped). Roughly chop the @coriander{5}(roughly chopped). Remove the seeds from the @red chilli{2} and finely chop.

Heat @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Cook the onion, garlic and chilli for about ~{6%minutes} or until soft.

> Tip: The amount of chilli you use depends on how hot you like things!

> Tip: Be careful not to burn them, if the pan is getting dry add a few drops of water.

Tip the onion mixture onto a #plate{} and keep to the side. Turn the heat up to its highest and without adding any more oil, cook the peppers for ~{3-4%minutes} until slightly charred, remove from the pan and set aside with the onion mix.

Fry off the @British beef mince{500}(in two batches) in the same pan over high heat, seasoning with @salt{} and @pepper{} as you go.

> Tip: Doing it this way you don't overcrowd the pan and the meat can brown off instead of simply stewing.

On medium heat, add back in all the meat, onion mix and peppers. Add the @smoked paprika{1}, @red kidney beans{2}(drain free) along with the @tomato passata{2} and @water{200%ml}. Turn to low and let it simmer for at least ~{10%minutes} (add a little more water if it begins to dry out).

> Tip: Rinse out the tin from the kidney beans with the water to use all the sauce.

Mix your @sour cream{1} with the zest and juice from half the @lime{1}(half for juice and zest) and a pinch of @salt{}.

Serve up the chilli with the rice, top with the sour cream/lime mix, chopped coriander and a wedge of lime on the side.